reviews.text: I love this place! I go here often, and it never disappoints. If you get the wrong combinations it can taste weird, but I love the Utah sauce. Sometimes it can take a little while for the food to come out though. I definitely recommend!

I always love walking into Wok the Line. Not only are the smells amazing but the food tastes even better. It's the perfect meal when you looking for something healthy and tasteful. All the flavors come together to make something extraordinary.

I eat here maybe 1 or 2 times a week. I am always greeted when walking in. After ordering and being around this welcoming place for a few weeks the service and atmosphere gets better and better. The restaurant is always clean.

Francis, Sergio and Von are always here when I order food. They took it upon themselves to memorize my order making it super easy for me to walk in and get my good started. They genuinely care about their guests and are doing an amazing job. I live 15 minutes away and my food is still hot when I get home. I will continue coming here with the service and care Francis, Sergio and Von continue to give.

PS The food is amazing and I recommend trying a few different sauces every time to dial in what you really like.

I highly recommend Wok the Line. This was our first time here and it did not disappoint- it only made me wonder why I hadn‚Äôt been here sooner.

The menu is easy to understand and the ordering system is easy to follow. You order, pay, and then sit and wait for your food. We came on a Saturday night and there were maybe a handful of people ahead of us. There were three employees, only one was on the wok preparing the food. It looked understaffed.

We ended up waiting over 40 minutes for our food. When we got our food, I discovered that my order was incorrect. I took it up to the cashier and he said it was their mistake and they are understaffed. He said they would get my correct order out soon. I waited another 15 minutes or so for my correct order. The young man apologized for the wait, brought us some egg rolls and wontons, and said he was going to refund our order for the wait and mistakes. We really appreciated that and felt he handled the situation very well. I liked the ownership.

I think the food is delicious. It‚Äôs fresh, flavorful, and I love the fact it‚Äôs made in an open kitchen and made to order. They have a lot of sauce options too. The portions are generous for the price. I can see myself coming here more often now that I know how great it is.

I do wish, because it was about an hour or so wait total for my food, that they told you upfront how long the wait would be. I know and understand that a lot of small business are understaffed. I love supporting local but do wish there was some transparency upfront about the wait time. That‚Äôs all I would ask.

My photos aren‚Äôt doing this justice, the food was amazing!!

This is my second time eating here and will definitely be back for a third time! The same owner also owns Under Wraps in the same parking lot, both great lunch or dinner spots, definitely recommend checking them both out!

What I ordered was not great. I got noodles and rice with some veggies, steak and the General Orange Sauce. I would not recommend the sauce. It was overly sweet and something (I think it was the sauce) left a strange bitter taste and I couldn‚Äôt even finish my food. Wouldn‚Äôt try this again because it was also $20 for a bowl and drink. Not worth that price when I couldn‚Äôt even force myself to finish.
Probably better if you get a different sauce. Great concept but I did not like my choice at all.

Zhavon was attentive, patient, and ensured that every detail of my dish was prepared to perfection. Their knowledge of the menu and dedication to creating a positive dining experience truly elevated my visit.

negative.text: the amount of food is quite small for how much you pay. the mix in the bowls is off; too much sauce, wish there were fewer carbs and more of the veggies. ordering online there were no descriptions of sauces. at least two bowls (we ordered four) had misplaced items; there were mushrooms in a bowl that had not ordered them and peanuts in a bowl when no one had ordered them. thankfully there were no food allergies within the group (also the online ordering would have charged $1.20 in order to add an allergy request). the sauces were too sweet with no depth.
